WEBVTT

00:02.750 --> 00:04.960
[ Bell clanging ]

00:04.960 --> 00:07.080
[ Sea gulls squawking ]

00:07.080 --> 00:11.670
♪♪

00:11.670 --> 00:14.080
[ Electricity humming ]

00:14.080 --> 00:18.830
♪♪

00:18.830 --> 00:20.830
[ Humming continues ]

00:20.830 --> 00:27.500
♪♪

00:27.500 --> 00:33.960
♪♪

00:33.960 --> 00:36.790
♪♪

00:36.790 --> 00:39.710
[ Safety pin scrapes ]

00:39.710 --> 00:41.080
♪♪

00:41.080 --> 00:45.500
[ Sea gull squawking ]

00:50.290 --> 00:51.380
[ Humming stops ]

00:51.380 --> 00:57.500
♪♪

00:57.500 --> 01:01.290
[ Projectile whistling,
crash in distance ]

01:01.290 --> 01:04.330
♪♪

01:04.330 --> 01:06.750
Mia: Mom?
What was that?

01:06.750 --> 01:08.380
Yeah, hold on.

01:08.380 --> 01:09.750
Ed:
Power's out.

01:09.750 --> 01:11.000
Yeah.

01:12.960 --> 01:21.710
♪♪

01:21.710 --> 01:27.250
♪♪

01:27.250 --> 01:29.380
[ Electricity humming ]

01:29.380 --> 01:31.420
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

01:33.710 --> 01:35.790
Yeah, I see it.

01:35.790 --> 01:37.330
I'm on my way.

01:37.330 --> 01:39.420
[ Dog barks in distance ]

01:39.420 --> 01:40.790
I got to get dressed
and go in to work.

01:40.790 --> 01:41.830
You guys should
go back to bed.

01:41.830 --> 01:42.830
Can I come?

01:42.830 --> 01:44.170
Sure can't.
Bed.

01:44.170 --> 01:45.620
What is it?
I'll call you.

01:45.620 --> 01:47.710
Come on.

01:47.710 --> 01:57.710
♪♪

01:57.710 --> 01:59.080
♪♪

01:59.080 --> 02:02.750
[ Sirens wail ]

02:02.750 --> 02:05.250
[ Indistinct conversations ]

02:05.250 --> 02:06.580
[ Radio chatter ]

02:06.580 --> 02:16.040
♪♪

02:16.040 --> 02:17.000
Chris:
Hey, Chief.

02:17.000 --> 02:18.500
Jo:
What do we got?

02:18.500 --> 02:19.750
We're thinking it's
a mid-sized private jet.

02:19.750 --> 02:21.540
10-passenger, tops.

02:21.540 --> 02:23.000
FAA's trying to figure out
who it was.

02:23.000 --> 02:24.790
Uh, closest airport's
Mattituck,

02:24.790 --> 02:26.290
and they're not
missing anybody.

02:26.290 --> 02:28.040
And then the PSEG's

02:28.040 --> 02:29.210
looking
into the blackout.

02:29.210 --> 02:30.330
They think the --
the plane

02:30.330 --> 02:31.540
might have clipped
one of their lines.

02:31.540 --> 02:32.540
Couldn't explain why

02:32.540 --> 02:34.330
my cellphone
stopped working, though.

02:34.330 --> 02:36.460
Well, uh, there's a cell tower
about a mile away,

02:36.460 --> 02:38.210
so the telecom company's
already investigating.

02:38.210 --> 02:40.380
Alright.
Set up a perimeter.

02:40.380 --> 02:42.000
Start canvassing
for witnesses.

02:42.000 --> 02:43.790
I'll get Parks
to shut down the beach.

02:43.790 --> 02:44.540
You got it.

02:44.540 --> 02:46.620
Good work.

02:48.920 --> 02:51.960
[ Waves crashing ]

02:51.960 --> 03:01.580
♪♪

03:01.580 --> 03:07.540
♪♪

03:07.540 --> 03:13.250
♪♪

03:13.250 --> 03:15.250
Are you okay?

03:15.250 --> 03:17.540
Are you hurt?

03:17.540 --> 03:25.120
♪♪

03:25.120 --> 03:27.000
Kind of cold out here.

03:27.000 --> 03:29.040
You want to maybe
borrow my coat?

03:30.880 --> 03:32.290
Chris: Chief.

03:32.290 --> 03:33.460
Every-- Everything
alright, or...?

03:33.460 --> 03:35.170
Yeah.

03:35.170 --> 03:37.290
Everything's fine.

03:37.290 --> 03:38.500
I'm just talking
to my new friend here.

03:38.500 --> 03:40.710
Hey.

03:40.710 --> 03:42.330
You like that movie?

03:43.830 --> 03:45.250
I love it.

03:45.250 --> 03:48.380
You know who
my favorite character is?

03:48.380 --> 03:49.580
Woody.

03:49.580 --> 03:52.250
♪♪

03:52.250 --> 03:54.540
You see this
right here?

03:54.540 --> 03:58.000
♪♪

03:58.000 --> 04:00.290
Yeah,
I'm like Woody.

04:00.290 --> 04:01.750
Okay?

04:01.750 --> 04:04.380
So I can help you.

04:04.380 --> 04:05.670
Alright?

04:08.000 --> 04:09.960
Why don't you
come here?

04:09.960 --> 04:11.380
It's okay.

04:11.380 --> 04:13.500
Come on.

04:13.500 --> 04:16.290
♪♪

04:16.290 --> 04:18.500
Ooh! Okay.

04:18.500 --> 04:19.500
Okay.

04:19.500 --> 04:21.000
Was she
on the plane?

04:21.000 --> 04:23.330
I don't know.

04:23.330 --> 04:24.710
Can I get a paramedic
over here?

04:24.710 --> 04:26.000
Paramedic!

04:26.000 --> 04:27.380
We just need to have them
look you over, okay?

04:27.380 --> 04:28.460
Make sure
you're not hurt.

04:28.460 --> 04:29.790
So, can you let go of me
for one second?

04:30.960 --> 04:33.210
No?
NTSB is here.

04:33.210 --> 04:34.380
They're saying they need
to clear everybody out.

04:36.420 --> 04:37.750
Alright, uh, yeah,
I'll handle it.

04:37.750 --> 04:39.000
Go ahead.

04:39.000 --> 04:41.540
Okay, um, can you just
have someone

04:41.540 --> 04:43.170
take my car
by the hospital later?

04:43.170 --> 04:44.250
Thanks.

04:44.250 --> 04:45.670
Alright,
we're gonna go together.

04:45.670 --> 04:47.830
I'm coming with you.
Come on.

04:47.830 --> 04:50.210
Abby: Good news is
she's physically fine.

04:50.210 --> 04:51.880
No contusions,
no head trauma,

04:51.880 --> 04:53.500
not even
a paper cut.

04:53.500 --> 04:56.080
Bad news is she says
she doesn't remember anything.

04:56.080 --> 04:57.120
She doesn't know
her name,

04:57.120 --> 04:58.620
doesn't know
where she's from.

04:58.620 --> 04:59.830
You think that's real?

04:59.830 --> 05:01.580
I sent her
for a head CT,

05:01.580 --> 05:04.380
but my guess is that
it's dissociative amnesia.

05:04.380 --> 05:06.080
Something
traumatic happened,

05:06.080 --> 05:08.420
and her brain
is protecting itself.

05:08.420 --> 05:10.750
What, something traumatic
like a plane crash?

05:10.750 --> 05:12.580
I don't see
how that's possible.

05:12.580 --> 05:14.710
She doesn't have
a scratch on her.

05:15.710 --> 05:18.080
There she is!

05:18.080 --> 05:19.500
Wasn't so scary,
was it?

05:20.920 --> 05:22.170
Man:
Oh, she did great.

05:22.170 --> 05:23.880
Super brave.

05:23.880 --> 05:26.080
Thanks.

05:26.080 --> 05:28.750
Well,
everything looks great.

05:28.750 --> 05:31.960
You are
a perfectly healthy girl.

05:31.960 --> 05:33.960
Can I go home?

05:33.960 --> 05:36.500
I would love that.

05:36.500 --> 05:37.710
Where's home?

05:37.710 --> 05:39.250
[ Telephone rings in distance ]

05:39.250 --> 05:41.210
[ Indistinct announcement
over P.A. ]

05:43.790 --> 05:44.920
[ Chuckles nervously ]

05:44.920 --> 05:46.290
That's a great choice.

05:46.290 --> 05:48.290
Maybe Jo can
stay with you

05:48.290 --> 05:51.380
until you
fall asleep, hmm?

05:51.380 --> 05:52.580
Yeah.

05:52.580 --> 05:55.420
I can absolutely
do that.

05:55.420 --> 05:57.790
I'm hoping
the memory will come back

05:57.790 --> 05:59.620
in the next day
or so.

05:59.620 --> 06:02.540
Yeah. Thanks.
Yeah.

06:02.540 --> 06:04.830
[ Siren wails in distance ]

06:08.170 --> 06:10.210
[ Sighs ]

06:12.790 --> 06:15.790
Oh, I, uh,
stopped by the vending machine

06:15.790 --> 06:18.210
while they were
looking inside your head.

06:19.580 --> 06:20.580
You know candy?

06:20.580 --> 06:21.790
[ Chuckles softly ]
Okay.

06:21.790 --> 06:23.000
It's good to know
you remember

06:23.000 --> 06:24.500
the really important
stuff.

06:24.500 --> 06:26.460
Let's see.

06:28.460 --> 06:29.580
What color?

06:29.580 --> 06:30.620
Let me see.

06:30.620 --> 06:31.920
Guess.

06:31.920 --> 06:33.290
[ Inhales sharply ]

06:33.290 --> 06:35.580
Red.

06:35.580 --> 06:36.960
Yellow.

06:39.080 --> 06:41.710
Again?

06:41.710 --> 06:42.710
Yellow.

06:42.710 --> 06:43.670
Mnh. Green.

06:43.670 --> 06:44.670
Ugh.

06:44.670 --> 06:46.290
Not fair.

06:46.290 --> 06:48.170
It's not my fault
that you're bad at this game.

06:48.170 --> 06:49.460
[ Candy pieces rattle ]

06:50.830 --> 06:52.080
Red.

06:52.080 --> 06:54.000
I mean purple.
Purple.

06:54.000 --> 06:55.960
Okay, I'm gonna give this
to you...

06:55.960 --> 06:58.210
Yes!
...this one time.

06:58.210 --> 07:00.500
But you really need
to practice, okay,

07:00.500 --> 07:02.790
'cause you're terrible
at this.
[ Indistinct shouting
in distance ]

07:02.790 --> 07:03.790
Can we do
another one?

07:03.790 --> 07:05.330
Um, you know what?

07:05.330 --> 07:07.250
You can practice by yourself,
but don't have too many,

07:07.250 --> 07:08.460
and I will be
right back.

07:08.460 --> 07:09.710
Okay?
Stay here.

07:09.710 --> 07:10.750
Officer: Doctor,
you are interfering...

07:10.750 --> 07:11.790
Abby: You don't
have any right...

07:11.790 --> 07:13.250
...with a
federal investigation.

07:13.250 --> 07:15.000
...to her private
medical files!
What is this?

07:15.000 --> 07:16.170
They're demanding
to speak with her

07:16.170 --> 07:17.790
and look at
her chart.
Okay.

07:17.790 --> 07:19.460
Hi. I'm Police Chief
Jo Evans.

07:19.460 --> 07:20.580
Who are you?

07:20.580 --> 07:23.170
Sir, you will be
in federal lockup tonight

07:23.170 --> 07:24.290
if you don't
get out of my way.

07:24.290 --> 07:26.210
Let's see how
that goes for you.

07:26.210 --> 07:29.250
NTSB doesn't have
arrest authority. I do.

07:29.250 --> 07:31.120
Escort these men
out of here.

07:31.120 --> 07:33.210
Listen, why don't we just
go down to the waiting room,

07:33.210 --> 07:35.790
and then you guys can tell me
what the hell's going on.

07:35.790 --> 07:37.380
Okay?
Abby:
She's gone!

07:37.380 --> 07:40.500
♪♪

07:40.500 --> 07:41.620
Jo: Station teams
at every exit.

07:41.620 --> 07:42.880
This is a code yellow.
Female aged 10.

07:42.880 --> 07:44.210
I want eyes on everyone
coming and going.

07:44.210 --> 07:45.580
Brown hair, blue eyes.
Be systematic.

07:45.580 --> 07:47.790
Every room. Every floor.
Go.

07:47.790 --> 07:49.290
Frankie, I need you to look
at the security footage

07:49.290 --> 07:50.380
for the last hour.

07:50.380 --> 07:52.170
Lopez, I want radio cars
along Route 25,

07:52.170 --> 07:53.500
and issue
an Amber Alert.

07:53.500 --> 07:55.380
Harbor's not far.
Kid could have fallen in.

07:55.380 --> 07:57.000
Yeah,
call the Marine Unit.

07:57.000 --> 07:58.420
Tell them
to get a boat out there.
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

07:58.420 --> 07:59.750
Evans.

07:59.750 --> 08:02.420
Hey, uh, Chief, I'm --
I'm still at the crash site,

08:02.420 --> 08:05.170
and, uh...
NTSB is here?

08:05.170 --> 08:07.120
Yeah, I know.
I'm aware of that, Chris.

08:07.120 --> 08:09.380
Yeah, no, no.
It's -- It's, uh --

08:09.380 --> 08:13.210
It's kind of
a different NTSB.

08:13.210 --> 08:16.330
And nobody knows
who those first guys were.

08:16.330 --> 08:26.330
♪♪

08:26.330 --> 08:29.380
[ Keys clacking ]

08:29.380 --> 08:32.040
[ Engine sputtering ]

08:32.040 --> 08:33.170
Come on!

08:33.170 --> 08:35.120
God,
you got to be kidding me.

08:35.120 --> 08:37.290
[ Keys clack, sputtering stops ]

08:37.290 --> 08:44.330
♪♪

08:44.330 --> 08:47.330
[ Heartbeat pounding ]
What?

08:47.330 --> 08:49.580
[ Engine starts, siren chirps ]

08:49.580 --> 08:51.580
Don't be mad.
[ Gasps ]

08:51.580 --> 08:54.290
[ Breathing heavily ]

09:01.750 --> 09:04.120
[ Door opens ]

09:04.120 --> 09:05.420
Jo: Get in.
[ Door closes ]

09:05.420 --> 09:06.620
We'll get you to bed,

09:06.620 --> 09:07.960
and we'll figure
everything out tomorrow, okay?

09:07.960 --> 09:09.210
Hey, pal.

09:09.210 --> 09:11.580
Dad, you shouldn't have
stayed up.

09:11.580 --> 09:13.170
Eh,
you know I don't sleep.

09:13.170 --> 09:15.830
How'd it go?
Oh.

09:15.830 --> 09:17.000
Hello.

09:17.000 --> 09:18.790
[ Sighs ]
We have a guest.

09:18.790 --> 09:19.960
I see that.

09:19.960 --> 09:21.210
[ Sighs ]

09:21.210 --> 09:22.580
Alright,
let's get you to bed, okay?

09:22.580 --> 09:23.750
I'm not tired.

09:23.750 --> 09:25.620
Okay, well,

09:25.620 --> 09:27.380
we're gonna...
try anyway, okay?

09:27.380 --> 09:29.960
Let's try to see
if we can find you some PJs.

09:29.960 --> 09:33.210
♪♪

09:33.210 --> 09:36.330
Who the hell runs around
impersonating NTSB?

09:36.330 --> 09:38.750
You think
she was on the plane?

09:40.040 --> 09:42.420
I don't know.

09:42.420 --> 09:44.210
Abby didn't think so.
I-I don't know.

09:44.210 --> 09:46.790
She belongs
to somebody.

09:46.790 --> 09:48.710
Gonna have to report her to
Family Services in the morning.

09:48.710 --> 09:50.170
Yeah, I mean,
I know that's the protocol,

09:50.170 --> 09:51.580
but if I put her
in the system,

09:51.580 --> 09:53.710
then whoever's looking for her
is gonna be able to find her.

09:53.710 --> 09:55.580
So, what are you gonna do?
Keep a kid you just found?

09:55.580 --> 09:56.580
[ Scoffs ]
For how long?

09:56.580 --> 09:57.710
A-And what's
the plan here?

09:57.710 --> 10:00.330
I don't have a plan.
Dad, I...

10:00.330 --> 10:02.080
I-I didn't know
what else to do.

10:03.710 --> 10:05.500
[ Sighs ]

10:05.500 --> 10:06.580
Well, you did
the only thing you could do.

10:06.580 --> 10:09.920
Or I kidnapped a kid.
No. No.

10:09.920 --> 10:12.620
She's safe. You're safe.
That's what's important.

10:12.620 --> 10:14.580
We'll figure it out
in the morning.

10:14.580 --> 10:16.000
Come on, honey.
Yeah.

10:18.790 --> 10:27.080
♪♪

10:27.080 --> 10:32.790
♪♪

10:32.790 --> 10:34.670
[ Children laughing ]

10:34.670 --> 10:36.500
[ Sighs ]

10:39.250 --> 10:42.210
[ Laughing continues ]

10:42.210 --> 10:44.830
Okay, would you rather be
a unicorn or a wizard?

10:45.880 --> 10:47.210
Girl: Unicorn.

10:47.210 --> 10:49.170
Obviously.

10:49.170 --> 10:50.830
Would you rather have no thumbs
or only thumbs?

10:50.830 --> 10:52.710
Morning.
Hey.

10:52.710 --> 10:55.040
So, what's, uh --

10:55.040 --> 10:56.380
What's everybody
doing, huh?

10:56.380 --> 10:58.120
Oh, Mom, okay --
what do you like better --

10:58.120 --> 11:00.330
Ariana or Millie?

11:00.330 --> 11:01.830
What are we
talking about?

11:01.830 --> 11:04.170
She needs a name.

11:04.170 --> 11:06.120
Well, honey, I imagine
that she already has one.

11:06.120 --> 11:07.420
She can't remember,

11:07.420 --> 11:09.620
and we have to
call her something.

11:09.620 --> 11:11.040
[ Sea gull squawks in distance ]

11:13.330 --> 11:15.750
Well, what name
do you like?

11:15.750 --> 11:18.580
I can't decide.
[ Chuckles ]

11:18.580 --> 11:20.250
You know
what I always liked?

11:20.250 --> 11:21.880
Piper.
That was almost your name.

11:21.880 --> 11:23.380
I like that one.

11:23.380 --> 11:24.540
Mia:
I love it.

11:24.540 --> 11:26.710
I kind of love it
more than my name,

11:26.710 --> 11:28.120
but whatever.

11:28.120 --> 11:31.420
Well,
life is hard, kid.
[ Chuckles ]

11:31.420 --> 11:33.330
I've got to meet Whitaker
before class.

11:33.330 --> 11:34.920
Mom,
we got to go.
Okay.

11:34.920 --> 11:36.830
See you later,
Piper.

11:36.830 --> 11:38.960
[ Footsteps depart ]

11:38.960 --> 11:40.330
Hey, Dad, um...
Mm-hmm?

11:40.330 --> 11:41.580
Chris called,

11:41.580 --> 11:43.790
and he said the NTSB's
cleared out already,

11:43.790 --> 11:45.210
which doesn't make
any sense.
Yeah.

11:45.210 --> 11:46.710
So I need to go
back to the site.

11:46.710 --> 11:48.000
Okay.

11:48.000 --> 11:50.170
You think that you guys
will be...

11:50.170 --> 11:51.500
you know...

11:51.500 --> 11:53.250
Oh, yeah, yeah.
We'll be okay.

11:53.250 --> 11:55.330
I got a lot of projects
to do today.

11:55.330 --> 11:56.210
Could really use
a helper.

12:01.540 --> 12:02.880
Okay.

12:02.880 --> 12:04.960
Thattagirl.

12:04.960 --> 12:09.790
♪♪

12:09.790 --> 12:11.670
[ Plates clacking ]
[ Clears throat ]

12:11.670 --> 12:13.420
Um, hey, Dad?

12:13.420 --> 12:14.500
Listen.
I'll be fine.

12:14.500 --> 12:16.000
I'll be fine.
I'm feeling good.

12:16.000 --> 12:18.580
Doc said I need to resume
normal activities, so...

12:18.580 --> 12:20.670
No, no, I know.
I'm just -- I'm saying, um...

12:20.670 --> 12:23.170
♪♪

12:23.170 --> 12:25.500
You know,
maybe just...

12:25.500 --> 12:27.210
stay near the house.

12:27.210 --> 12:31.210
Or in -- in --
in the house.

12:31.210 --> 12:32.750
Alright.

12:32.750 --> 12:34.380
Okay.

12:34.380 --> 12:36.420
And, um --

12:36.420 --> 12:38.790
Mia:
Mom, we got to go!
Yeah.
I'm coming.

12:38.790 --> 12:40.380
Um, Chris knows she's here,
so just call him or call me.

12:40.380 --> 12:42.080
Okay?

12:42.080 --> 12:43.080
Alright.
I'm gonna go.

12:43.080 --> 12:44.000
Bye. Bye.
Bye. Bye.

12:46.580 --> 12:47.960
You're being really sweet
with her,

12:47.960 --> 12:49.790
and I think it helps,
so thank you.

12:49.790 --> 12:51.210
It's easy.
She's cute.

12:51.210 --> 12:53.210
Yeah, well,
she's not gonna be

12:53.210 --> 12:54.960
crashing with us
for very long, so...

12:54.960 --> 12:56.380
I don't mind.

12:56.380 --> 12:58.210
It's, like, the only way
I'll get a little sister

12:58.210 --> 13:00.210
now that you and Dad
aren't together.

13:02.170 --> 13:04.960
[ Car door opens, closes ]

13:04.960 --> 13:09.540
♪♪

13:09.540 --> 13:10.960
[ Horn honks ]

13:10.960 --> 13:13.750
Mom!
Hurry up!

13:13.750 --> 13:17.170
Ed: This one,
I take in the morning.

13:17.170 --> 13:19.920
Uh, but it
makes me thirsty.

13:19.920 --> 13:24.960
These make hair
grow all over me.

13:24.960 --> 13:26.580
Kind of psyched
about that

13:26.580 --> 13:29.580
'cause I always
wanted to be a werewolf.

13:29.580 --> 13:31.580
[ Howls ]

13:31.580 --> 13:33.210
Why do you take
all these?

13:35.830 --> 13:39.500
Well, uh,
I used to be a firefighter,

13:39.500 --> 13:44.290
and I was around a lot of
bad stuff that burned.

13:44.290 --> 13:48.120
And I got
something called cancer.

13:48.120 --> 13:51.000
These are
making me better.

13:52.170 --> 13:53.710
No, they're not.

13:53.710 --> 13:58.540
♪♪

13:58.540 --> 14:01.210
O-kay.

14:01.210 --> 14:03.380
[ Glass thuds ]

14:03.380 --> 14:06.210
So, I don't suppose
you know

14:06.210 --> 14:08.540
how to install
a garbage disposal, do you?

14:08.540 --> 14:10.040
No.

14:10.040 --> 14:13.920
[ Inhales deeply ]
Okay.

14:13.920 --> 14:19.000
Now, this here --
a socket wrench.

14:19.000 --> 14:20.580
There's one
about your size.

14:20.580 --> 14:23.790
Oh, this -- this is
a needle-nose plier.

14:23.790 --> 14:26.830
And my Allen wrench
must be in the basement.

14:26.830 --> 14:29.170
I'll be right back.

14:29.170 --> 14:31.170
Don't start
without me.

14:33.790 --> 14:36.960
[ Socket wrench clicks ]

14:36.960 --> 14:39.790
[ Static crackling ]

14:39.790 --> 14:45.040
♪♪

14:45.040 --> 14:47.790
[ Crackling continues ]

14:47.790 --> 14:57.830
♪♪

14:57.830 --> 15:07.670
♪♪

15:07.670 --> 15:10.620
[ Crackling intensifies ]

15:10.620 --> 15:13.420
♪♪

15:13.420 --> 15:15.170
Piper.

15:15.170 --> 15:16.920
Piper?

15:16.920 --> 15:18.920
Piper?

15:18.920 --> 15:20.670
Ah.

15:20.670 --> 15:22.170
[ TV chatter ]

15:22.170 --> 15:23.960
Did you forget
your new name already?

15:23.960 --> 15:26.420
Oh.
I didn't hear you.

15:26.420 --> 15:27.830
Sorry.

15:27.830 --> 15:31.210
Well,
that's okay.

15:31.210 --> 15:31.960
Reporter:
...looking at a combin--

15:31.960 --> 15:33.380
[ TV shuts off ]

15:33.380 --> 15:34.790
[ Remote thuds ]

15:34.790 --> 15:37.040
Alright, you have my tools?
Oh, no, there they are.

15:37.040 --> 15:40.000
Alright, let's get to work,
little girl.

15:40.000 --> 15:45.960
♪♪

15:45.960 --> 15:48.000
[ Tools clack ]

15:48.000 --> 15:54.920
♪♪

15:58.540 --> 16:00.460
[ Sea gulls squawking ]
Jo: Excuse me.

16:00.460 --> 16:02.670
Are you NTSB?

16:02.670 --> 16:05.170
[ British accent ]
Me? Oh, no.

16:05.170 --> 16:06.830
Yikes.
Definitely not.

16:07.880 --> 16:09.120
Well,
who are you?

16:09.120 --> 16:11.250
I'm Benny.

16:12.540 --> 16:14.880
Sir, come up here
and show me some identification.

16:14.880 --> 16:17.000
Now.
Okay. Sure.

16:18.460 --> 16:19.790
Here you go.

16:19.790 --> 16:21.620
Oh, that's my
business card.

16:21.620 --> 16:23.080
And, uh,
there's my ID.

16:28.710 --> 16:30.710
You can't be here.
This is a restricted area.

16:30.710 --> 16:33.000
Not so much anymore.

16:33.000 --> 16:35.120
The National Transportation
Safety Board's

16:35.120 --> 16:37.420
so-called investigation
is complete.

16:37.420 --> 16:40.420
And they cleaned it all up
for you to be helpful.

16:40.420 --> 16:42.580
Nah, I'm kidding.
That's not what they did.

16:42.580 --> 16:45.210
It is super weird.

16:46.790 --> 16:48.830
Get out of here,
Mr. Gallagher.

16:48.830 --> 16:51.170
I know what
the report's gonna say.

16:51.170 --> 16:54.380
They're gonna say
it was an unmanned drone

16:54.380 --> 16:57.000
monitoring pollution,
mapping forests.

16:57.000 --> 16:58.330
Some rubbish like that.

16:58.330 --> 17:00.120
How do you know that?

17:00.120 --> 17:01.670
I have sources.

17:01.670 --> 17:04.620
Sources that
you don't have.

17:04.620 --> 17:06.620
You and I can
share information.

17:06.620 --> 17:08.000
I doubt very much

17:08.000 --> 17:09.960
that you have any information
that I want.

17:09.960 --> 17:11.580
What about where the plane
took off from?

17:11.580 --> 17:13.330
♪♪

17:13.330 --> 17:16.620
It took off
from Plum Island,

17:16.620 --> 17:19.460
about three miles
off the tip of the North Fork.

17:19.460 --> 17:20.670
You know
what's on that island?

17:20.670 --> 17:22.250
Everyone knows
what's on that island.

17:22.250 --> 17:23.960
Homeland Secur--
Homeland Security
research facility.

17:23.960 --> 17:24.960
Boom.
That's weird.

17:27.790 --> 17:29.080
Do you have proof?

17:29.080 --> 17:31.170
Not yet.
But I'm right.

17:32.960 --> 17:34.960
Okay.

17:34.960 --> 17:37.250
Cool story.

17:37.250 --> 17:38.830
You know, usually,

17:38.830 --> 17:40.540
local law enforcement
really likes me.

17:40.540 --> 17:42.460
Just this thing
that kind of happens.

17:42.460 --> 17:44.210
We're laying
the foundations

17:44.210 --> 17:45.790
for a perfect
working relationship.

17:45.790 --> 17:48.580
Gonna be great!

17:48.580 --> 17:52.830
♪♪

17:52.830 --> 17:55.000
Hey. Hi.

17:55.000 --> 17:57.380
Ed: Grab a plate.
Spaghetti and meatballs.
Sorry, Alex.

17:57.380 --> 17:59.170
I meant to call you and tell you
that we had company.

17:59.170 --> 18:00.500
Well,
Mia explained it.

18:00.500 --> 18:02.750
She also said she's gonna
stay here for the weekend.

18:02.750 --> 18:04.250
Wait, what?

18:04.250 --> 18:06.000
I just decided
I'm not leaving.

18:06.000 --> 18:08.250
It's way too traumatic
for Piper.

18:08.250 --> 18:10.670
Oh, it's --
it's too traumatic?

18:10.670 --> 18:13.000
Um, yeah.

18:13.000 --> 18:14.500
She needs security
and consistency,

18:14.500 --> 18:15.920
which is what
all children need,

18:15.920 --> 18:17.460
which I learned
from my therapist,

18:17.460 --> 18:19.000
so you should be
so psyched about that.

18:22.710 --> 18:24.670
This is the first
I've heard of this.

18:24.670 --> 18:26.250
And Dad's totally fine
with it.

18:26.250 --> 18:28.420
Well, we have a schedule
for a reason, sweetheart.

18:28.420 --> 18:30.040
Okay, but you're
absolutely right.

18:30.040 --> 18:31.960
It is important that
all of us are comfortable
with the arrangement.

18:31.960 --> 18:33.210
Okay, how about this,
alright?

18:33.210 --> 18:35.170
Next school break,
Dad's gonna take my days.

18:35.170 --> 18:37.170
You guys
can go fishing?

18:37.170 --> 18:38.960
Sounds like a plan.

18:38.960 --> 18:41.120
You're gonna
love fishing.

18:41.120 --> 18:42.170
Stick around
for dinner, Alex.

18:42.170 --> 18:43.080
Made that garlic bread
you like.

18:43.080 --> 18:44.170
Ed, thanks,
but I'm good.

18:44.170 --> 18:45.210
Hey, come here.

18:45.210 --> 18:46.250
Ohh!

18:46.250 --> 18:47.880
Yes!
Mia:
Ohh! [ Laughs ]

18:47.880 --> 18:49.330
That's a tight one.
I love you.

18:49.330 --> 18:51.210
I love you, too.
I'll see you later.

18:52.540 --> 18:54.460
Hey, listen,
I'm really sorry, honestly.

18:54.460 --> 18:56.420
I didn't know
that she was planning that.

18:56.420 --> 18:58.750
I don't understand
why we have a custody schedule

18:58.750 --> 19:00.170
if we're gonna break it
after two months.

19:00.170 --> 19:01.460
If you really
feel strongly about it,

19:01.460 --> 19:02.790
I will tell her
that she has to go with you.

19:02.790 --> 19:03.790
It's fine.
No.

19:03.790 --> 19:06.380
Don't -- No,
I want to be flexible.

19:06.380 --> 19:08.210
[ Sighs ]
What's going on?

19:08.210 --> 19:10.210
You fostering this kid
or something?

19:10.210 --> 19:14.080
No, I'm keeping her here...
temporarily.

19:14.080 --> 19:15.120
Unofficially.

19:16.670 --> 19:18.670
She's all alone. I mean,
I couldn't just abandon her.

19:18.670 --> 19:20.000
Okay.

19:20.000 --> 19:21.880
It all
makes sense now.

19:21.880 --> 19:24.120
Anybody would have
done this.
Oh,
if you say so.

19:24.120 --> 19:26.170
And it's temporary,
anyway.

19:26.170 --> 19:27.250
So temporary
that Mia thinks

19:27.250 --> 19:29.380
I'm taking them both fishing
next month.

19:31.000 --> 19:32.170
Well,
who doesn't like fishing?

19:32.170 --> 19:34.120
I mean,
you hate it.
I know.

19:34.120 --> 19:36.710
I feel bad
for the worm.

19:36.710 --> 19:38.960
I know.

19:38.960 --> 19:40.290
Okay,
I'll see you later.

19:40.290 --> 19:42.040
Okay.

19:44.080 --> 19:46.710
[ Sea gulls squawking ]

19:46.710 --> 19:48.380
[ Knock on door ]

19:48.380 --> 19:49.460
Hey.

19:49.460 --> 19:50.580
Got everything
you need?

19:50.580 --> 19:52.000
Yep.

19:52.000 --> 19:54.170
You know,
this used to be mine.

19:54.170 --> 19:56.290
And then
I gave it to Mia.

19:56.290 --> 19:57.580
But she's too big
for it now.

19:57.580 --> 20:00.420
She let me
borrow this, too.

20:00.420 --> 20:02.670
Wow!
That is one of her favorites.

20:02.670 --> 20:05.710
She must
really like you.

20:05.710 --> 20:08.500
So,
how did things go today?

20:10.170 --> 20:12.790
Did you...

20:12.790 --> 20:15.790
start to
remember anything?

20:17.380 --> 20:20.170
Would you rather
have hands for feet

20:20.170 --> 20:22.540
or feet for hands?

20:22.540 --> 20:23.670
Hmm.

20:23.670 --> 20:25.710
Hands for feet.

20:25.710 --> 20:27.080
Me, too.

20:27.080 --> 20:29.460
Mm. Mm-hmm.

20:32.420 --> 20:34.960
[ Inhales sharply,
sighs ]

20:34.960 --> 20:38.380
Do you think
maybe...

20:38.380 --> 20:40.210
that you're afraid
of remembering?

20:40.210 --> 20:42.620
I don't know.

20:42.620 --> 20:44.170
Hmm.

20:46.710 --> 20:48.920
I mean,
I would be,

20:48.920 --> 20:49.960
you know,
'cause you don't know.

20:49.960 --> 20:51.420
Could be...

20:51.420 --> 20:53.120
sad or scary.

20:53.120 --> 20:55.120
Maybe I won't
remember ever.

20:56.750 --> 20:58.750
Maybe.
Yeah.

21:06.500 --> 21:08.380
You know, um...

21:08.380 --> 21:13.250
♪♪

21:13.250 --> 21:15.710
Something really sad
happened to me

21:15.710 --> 21:16.920
when I was about
your age.

21:16.920 --> 21:19.620
What?

21:19.620 --> 21:23.790
Well, um...

21:23.790 --> 21:29.790
I got up one day
for school, and...

21:33.330 --> 21:37.040
...my mom was gone.

21:37.040 --> 21:39.580
And...

21:39.580 --> 21:42.960
she left a note

21:42.960 --> 21:45.040
saying she was going
on a trip.

21:47.750 --> 21:49.120
But...

21:52.000 --> 21:56.500
...she never --
she never came back.

22:00.830 --> 22:02.380
That's so sad.

22:02.380 --> 22:03.790
Yeah.

22:03.790 --> 22:06.540
It was.
It was really sad.

22:06.540 --> 22:09.380
♪♪

22:09.380 --> 22:10.380
[ Sniffles ]
And you know what?

22:10.380 --> 22:12.380
For a really long time,

22:12.380 --> 22:14.790
I didn't want
to talk about it,

22:14.790 --> 22:16.580
and I didn't even
want to think about it.

22:18.250 --> 22:22.960
But that didn't even
make me feel any better.

22:22.960 --> 22:25.330
Why?

22:25.330 --> 22:27.580
I think sometimes

22:27.580 --> 22:31.330
it helps to talk about things
that are scary or sad

22:31.330 --> 22:35.790
because then we know
that we're not alone.

22:35.790 --> 22:41.380
♪♪

22:41.380 --> 22:47.170
If I remember,
then I have to go away.

22:47.170 --> 22:50.170
And I want to stay.

22:50.170 --> 22:52.330
♪♪

22:52.330 --> 22:54.380
Hmm.

22:54.380 --> 22:56.500
Yeah.

22:56.500 --> 23:01.120
♪♪

23:01.120 --> 23:05.120
Well, you know,
I can pretty much guarantee

23:05.120 --> 23:07.250
that Mia's gonna
want that back.

23:07.250 --> 23:08.580
So I don't think
you're getting rid of us

23:08.580 --> 23:10.540
anytime soon.

23:10.540 --> 23:11.960
Okay?

23:11.960 --> 23:14.170
Okay.

23:14.170 --> 23:17.000
♪♪

23:17.000 --> 23:18.830
Yeah, it's, um,
getting late,

23:18.830 --> 23:21.500
so I think you should probably
get to bed, okay?

23:21.500 --> 23:23.000
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

23:23.000 --> 23:25.210
Hey, Chris.
What's up?

23:25.210 --> 23:27.250
Hey, uh,
you better get in here.

23:27.250 --> 23:28.330
Something wrong?

23:28.330 --> 23:30.620
No, I'm actually calling
with some good news.

23:30.620 --> 23:32.210
There's a man
and a woman in here,

23:32.210 --> 23:34.500
and they say
they're the girl's parents.

23:34.500 --> 23:39.080
♪♪

23:43.000 --> 23:45.380
Uh, so, names are
Freddie and Caitlyn Martin.

23:45.380 --> 23:47.000
Daughter, Olivia,
went missing

23:47.000 --> 23:48.710
at the campsite
last night.

23:48.710 --> 23:51.790
Uh, did you not,
uh, bring the kid?

23:51.790 --> 23:54.330
Why don't you get them
some coffee?

23:54.330 --> 23:55.380
Okay, Chris?

23:55.380 --> 23:56.960
Sure. Sure.
Sure thing.

23:56.960 --> 23:58.790
Mr. and Mrs. Martin?

23:58.790 --> 24:01.040
Hi.
Is Olivia alright?

24:01.040 --> 24:02.960
No one will
tell us anything.

24:02.960 --> 24:05.880
I think we've got
good news for you.
[ Sighs ]

24:05.880 --> 24:07.540
Oh, thank God.
[ Sighs ]

24:07.540 --> 24:10.420
Thank you, Chief Evans.
Thank you so much.

24:10.420 --> 24:12.420
Yeah.
We, um -- We --
We figured

24:12.420 --> 24:13.540
you'd want to see
some identification.

24:13.540 --> 24:14.790
Yeah.

24:14.790 --> 24:16.500
We only have
her passport with us,

24:16.500 --> 24:18.170
but we have her
birth certificate at home --

24:18.170 --> 24:19.380
whatever you need.

24:19.380 --> 24:21.170
That's okay.
Thank you.

24:21.170 --> 24:22.750
Thank you.

24:22.750 --> 24:24.540
Thank you.

24:24.540 --> 24:25.540
Hmm.

24:25.540 --> 24:27.580
Wow. Charlotte.

24:27.580 --> 24:29.710
What brings you guys
up to Long Island?

24:29.710 --> 24:31.170
I grew up nearby,

24:31.170 --> 24:32.960
so we came
to do some camping.

24:32.960 --> 24:34.500
Can we see Olivia?

24:34.500 --> 24:36.000
Mid-week camping?

24:36.000 --> 24:37.580
Middle of
the school year?

24:37.580 --> 24:39.790
Lucky kid.
[ Chuckles ]

24:39.790 --> 24:41.830
How did you guys
get separated?

24:41.830 --> 24:44.620
She was in the tent
when we went to sleep.

24:44.620 --> 24:48.420
Mm-hmm.
But, uh, when we woke up,
she was just gone.

24:48.420 --> 24:51.120
And we tried calling 911,
but we couldn't get through.

24:51.120 --> 24:53.500
So we just --
We drove here.

24:53.500 --> 24:56.790
I know you must think
we are terrible parents.

24:56.790 --> 24:59.420
No,
I don't think that.

24:59.420 --> 25:02.210
Honestly, kids --
you know, they wander off.

25:02.210 --> 25:03.920
I wish you guys
had called sooner.

25:03.920 --> 25:05.790
Like I said,
we tried,

25:05.790 --> 25:07.580
but there was no signal
out there.

25:07.580 --> 25:09.580
I mean, I -- Look,
I still don't have one.

25:09.580 --> 25:11.380
Yeah.

25:11.380 --> 25:15.330
I'm sorry.
How is the camera on that?

25:15.330 --> 25:16.580
It's fine.

25:16.580 --> 25:18.460
It's just like
a regular camera.

25:18.460 --> 25:21.500
I mean, I only ever take
pictures on my phone anymore,

25:21.500 --> 25:24.250
and my phone is just like
90% pictures of my kid.

25:24.250 --> 25:25.790
I'm sure yours
is the same way.

25:25.790 --> 25:27.750
Do you mind if I -- I'm thinking
about getting a new one.

25:27.750 --> 25:29.250
I just want to --

25:29.250 --> 25:30.620
Can I see
your pictures of Olivia?

25:30.620 --> 25:35.040
♪♪

25:35.040 --> 25:38.170
We've answered
your questions.

25:38.170 --> 25:40.170
I'd like
to see my daughter.

25:40.170 --> 25:41.380
Now.

25:41.380 --> 25:42.750
Of course.

25:42.750 --> 25:44.580
I apologize.

25:44.580 --> 25:47.380
I --
I'll be right back.

25:47.380 --> 25:48.670
[ Inhales sharply ]
You know what?

25:48.670 --> 25:52.380
And I will, um,
warm those up for you, too.

25:52.380 --> 25:55.330
Sorry about that.
Okay.

25:55.330 --> 25:57.210
Don't touch the sides.

25:57.210 --> 25:59.000
Pull prints.
Run them immediately.

25:59.000 --> 26:00.330
Wait, what ha--
what happened?

26:00.330 --> 26:03.000
They are not
who they say they are.

26:03.000 --> 26:06.460
They --
They had passports.
They had passp--

26:06.460 --> 26:09.210
[ Electricity hums,
electronics whirring ]

26:09.210 --> 26:15.790
♪♪

26:15.790 --> 26:18.750
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

26:21.670 --> 26:23.330
What's wrong?

26:23.330 --> 26:24.830
I need you to go over
to the house, okay,

26:24.830 --> 26:27.080
and -- and --
and get Mia and Dad and Piper.

26:27.080 --> 26:29.460
Yo. What the hell
is going on?

26:29.460 --> 26:31.290
Alex,
can you do this or not?

26:33.080 --> 26:34.710
Where do you want me
to take them?

26:34.710 --> 26:36.580
Go to the place

26:36.580 --> 26:39.500
where we set the kitchen
on fire.

26:39.500 --> 26:40.880
Do you know
what I'm talking about?

26:40.880 --> 26:42.500
Just say yes or no.

26:42.500 --> 26:44.380
Yeah. Jo --
Do not bring
your cellphone.

26:44.380 --> 26:45.710
What?

26:45.710 --> 26:47.250
I-I'll be there
as soon as I can.

26:47.250 --> 26:48.710
[ Click ]

26:51.290 --> 26:52.830
Alex: See?
[ Metal clacks ]

26:52.830 --> 26:55.210
How much fun is this?

26:55.210 --> 26:56.790
Right?
So much fun!

26:56.790 --> 26:58.170
It's like we're camping!

26:58.170 --> 27:00.170
Well,
but we're inside.

27:00.170 --> 27:03.000
Yeah, I love
middle-of-the-night beach trips

27:03.000 --> 27:04.330
on a school night.

27:04.330 --> 27:06.170
Ed: Got some hot-chocolate
fixings in there.

27:06.170 --> 27:07.540
Who wants some?

27:07.540 --> 27:09.580
Grandpa, seriously?

27:09.580 --> 27:10.960
Hot chocolate?

27:10.960 --> 27:13.420
[ Vehicle approaches ]

27:13.420 --> 27:15.120
I would like some.

27:15.120 --> 27:17.330
Well, I mean, yeah.
So would I.

27:17.330 --> 27:19.620
[ Car door closes ]
It's her.

27:19.620 --> 27:21.330
[ Door opens ]

27:21.330 --> 27:22.330
Hey, honey.

27:22.330 --> 27:23.380
Hey, Dad.

27:23.380 --> 27:24.380
Hey, Mom.

27:24.380 --> 27:26.620
Hi, sweetie.
Ooh!

27:26.620 --> 27:28.620
[ Lock clicks ]
Wow.
Looks so fun in here.

27:28.620 --> 27:30.080
Oh!

27:30.080 --> 27:31.670
We're having
hot chocolate.

27:31.670 --> 27:33.000
Oh,
that sounds great.

27:33.000 --> 27:35.080
I'll have
some of that, too.

27:35.080 --> 27:37.750
Jo.
Hey, um, um...

27:37.750 --> 27:39.670
it's --
this is a prepaid,

27:39.670 --> 27:42.880
just, you know,
so you have it
if you need it.

27:46.880 --> 27:48.920
[ Exhales
forcefully ]

27:48.920 --> 27:51.170
[ Fire crackling ]

27:57.330 --> 27:58.790
Well, I suppose
you're all wondering

27:58.790 --> 27:59.960
why I've called you
here today.

27:59.960 --> 28:01.710
Jo.
It's not funny.

28:01.710 --> 28:04.380
I'm sorry.

28:04.380 --> 28:06.170
Hmm.

28:06.170 --> 28:10.040
Okay [Clears throat]
um...

28:11.580 --> 28:13.580
So...

28:13.580 --> 28:19.170
tonight, two people
came by the station,

28:19.170 --> 28:21.170
and they said that
they were Piper's parents.

28:23.420 --> 28:24.920
But they were lying.

28:26.960 --> 28:30.500
I don't know
who they are.

28:30.500 --> 28:32.000
I don't know
why they're looking for you.

28:34.040 --> 28:37.960
But I'm gonna
find out, okay?

28:37.960 --> 28:39.460
Listen to me.

28:41.330 --> 28:44.380
I am not gonna
let them take you.

28:44.380 --> 28:46.420
Alright?

28:46.420 --> 28:48.920
I'm gonna
keep you safe.

28:48.920 --> 28:51.290
Why do they want
to take me?

28:51.290 --> 28:52.710
You know,
I don't know.

28:52.710 --> 28:56.920
But I bet the answer

28:56.920 --> 29:00.330
is right in here
somewhere.

29:02.080 --> 29:03.330
We all gonna sleep
in this room tonight?

29:03.330 --> 29:04.330
Ed: Sure.

29:04.330 --> 29:05.790
Safety in numbers.

29:05.790 --> 29:09.210
Uh, I got a couple of cots
in the hallway closet.

29:09.210 --> 29:10.380
Do you want
to help me with them?

29:10.380 --> 29:11.540
Jo: Yeah.

29:11.540 --> 29:14.210
I'll try
to remember.

29:14.210 --> 29:16.580
What?

29:16.580 --> 29:18.420
I'll try to remember.

29:18.420 --> 29:20.250
I'll try really hard.

29:20.250 --> 29:23.040
I know.
It's okay.

29:23.040 --> 29:27.420
♪♪

29:27.420 --> 29:30.170
I'm sorry. I didn't want
to pull you into this.

29:30.170 --> 29:31.580
I'm worried,
Jo.

29:31.580 --> 29:33.040
No,
it's okay.

29:33.040 --> 29:34.500
We're gonna be okay.
It's fine.

29:34.500 --> 29:35.880
That's not
why I'm worried.

29:35.880 --> 29:37.790
I'm worried because either
something's really messed up

29:37.790 --> 29:39.920
or you're
really paranoid.

29:39.920 --> 29:42.380
I see.
So I'm crazy.

29:42.380 --> 29:44.420
That's a good explanation
for you.

29:44.420 --> 29:46.380
Well, Jo,
you're not giving me one.

29:46.380 --> 29:48.170
All I see is you
pulling people out of bed

29:48.170 --> 29:49.620
in the middle
of the night

29:49.620 --> 29:51.250
and buying me
a damn burner phone.

29:51.250 --> 29:54.620
A plane crashed on the beach,
alright,

29:54.620 --> 29:57.170
and then was cleaned up
pretty much instantaneously.

29:57.170 --> 29:59.210
I found a kid
at the crash site

29:59.210 --> 30:01.170
I'm being told
wasn't even on the plane.

30:01.170 --> 30:02.460
Fake federal agents.

30:02.460 --> 30:05.670
Fake parents
that just vanish?

30:05.670 --> 30:07.420
I wish
I was being paranoid.

30:07.420 --> 30:11.290
Alex,
I don't think that I am.

30:11.290 --> 30:14.000
And don't tell --
don't tell me

30:14.000 --> 30:15.380
that I'm putting my family
in danger.

30:15.380 --> 30:16.380
I'm not saying that.

30:16.380 --> 30:17.710
I didn't know
what else to do.

30:17.710 --> 30:19.170
I'm not saying that,
okay?

30:19.170 --> 30:20.830
I'm not saying that.
I'm here.

30:22.330 --> 30:24.170
I'm here to help.

30:26.170 --> 30:27.170
Thank you.

30:27.170 --> 30:29.210
[ Soft thud ]

30:29.210 --> 30:31.580
Mia: Mom,
what was that?

30:31.580 --> 30:32.500
Mom!

30:36.120 --> 30:38.420
♪♪

30:38.420 --> 30:40.170
What --
W-What was that?

30:40.170 --> 30:43.170
Shh. Shh.
Okay. Shh.

30:43.170 --> 30:45.710
[ Floorboards creaking ]

30:45.710 --> 30:47.880
Somebody's
out there.

30:47.880 --> 30:55.920
♪♪

30:55.920 --> 30:59.330
[ Doorknob rattles ]

30:59.330 --> 31:09.380
♪♪

31:09.380 --> 31:19.380
♪♪

31:19.380 --> 31:23.170
♪♪

31:23.170 --> 31:24.960
[ Whispering ]
Right here.

31:24.960 --> 31:30.710
♪♪

31:30.710 --> 31:36.250
♪♪

31:36.250 --> 31:40.080
♪♪

31:40.080 --> 31:43.210
[ Glass shatters ]
[ Exhales sharply ]

31:44.830 --> 31:47.580
[ Footsteps, glass crunching ]

31:47.580 --> 31:57.580
♪♪

31:57.580 --> 31:59.500
♪♪

31:59.500 --> 32:01.000
Go, go.
Go, go, go.

32:01.000 --> 32:02.420
[ Shoes squeaking ]

32:02.420 --> 32:03.460
[ Door opens ]

32:03.460 --> 32:06.670
[ Piper panting, whimpering ]

32:06.670 --> 32:09.170
[ Flashlight clicks ]

32:09.170 --> 32:10.580
Come on.

32:10.580 --> 32:11.710
Stay down.
[ Whimpers ]

32:11.710 --> 32:13.420
Ed: Get a blanket.

32:13.420 --> 32:15.880
Stand back.
Cover your eyes.

32:17.580 --> 32:19.710
You ready?
Yeah.

32:19.710 --> 32:21.000
Two, three.

32:21.000 --> 32:22.420
[ Glass shatters ]
[ Screams ]

32:22.420 --> 32:25.500
[ Pounding on door ]
Police! I'm armed!

32:25.500 --> 32:27.170
[ Electricity buzzing ]
Man: Now!

32:27.170 --> 32:32.750
♪♪

32:32.750 --> 32:33.710
[ Glass shatters ]

32:33.710 --> 32:36.710
♪♪

32:36.710 --> 32:38.040
[ Whimpers ]

32:38.040 --> 32:39.670
♪♪

32:39.670 --> 32:42.420
Mom,
what's happening?!

32:42.420 --> 32:44.380
[ Objects clattering ]

32:48.250 --> 32:50.040
Let's go!
Let's go!

32:50.040 --> 32:51.920
Alex:
Come on!

32:51.920 --> 32:53.330
Okay.
Alex, you first.

32:53.330 --> 32:54.330
Alright.
Come on.

32:54.330 --> 32:55.830
Ed: Let's go.
Let's go.

32:55.830 --> 32:57.790
Come on. Hi.

32:57.790 --> 32:58.790
Go on.
Go, go, go, go, go.

32:58.790 --> 32:59.790
Sweetie.
Sweetie,
you're next.

32:59.790 --> 33:00.880
[ Whimpers ]

33:00.880 --> 33:02.620
It's okay.
It's okay.
Go, go, go, go, go.

33:02.620 --> 33:04.040
Dad,
you're next.

33:04.040 --> 33:05.790
Like hell.

33:05.790 --> 33:07.830
[ Grunts ]

33:07.830 --> 33:09.170
Mia:
Mom! Come quick!
Come on.

33:09.170 --> 33:11.170
I'm good. Go. Go.

33:11.170 --> 33:12.170
[ Alex grunts ]

33:12.170 --> 33:14.080
Jo: What happened?
I'm alright.

33:14.080 --> 33:16.420
Someone hit me.
Where's Piper?

33:16.420 --> 33:17.960
[ Engine revs ]
Mom, you have to go
get her!

33:17.960 --> 33:19.620
Piper!
[ Tires squeal ]

33:19.620 --> 33:21.170
[ Radio chirps, siren wailing ]
Dispatch, this is Evans.

33:21.170 --> 33:22.170
Operator:
Go ahead, Chief.

33:22.170 --> 33:23.620
Child abduction in progress.

33:23.620 --> 33:25.960
I need all available units
to the utility road

33:25.960 --> 33:27.380
parallel to County Road 48.

33:27.380 --> 33:28.880
[ Engine revving ]
Copy, Chief.

33:28.880 --> 33:30.830
All available units,
support for the utility road

33:30.830 --> 33:32.920
parallel to
County Road 48.

33:32.920 --> 33:34.080
Child abduction
in progress.

33:34.080 --> 33:35.540
Officers...

33:35.540 --> 33:36.750
[ Wailing continues ]

33:36.750 --> 33:40.080
♪♪

33:40.080 --> 33:43.290
[ Glass shatters ]

33:43.290 --> 33:44.620
[ Tires screech ]

33:44.620 --> 33:47.830
[ Panting ]

33:47.830 --> 33:54.460
♪♪

33:54.460 --> 34:04.540
♪♪

34:04.540 --> 34:07.500
♪♪

34:07.500 --> 34:08.880
[ Steam hissing ]

34:08.880 --> 34:14.710
♪♪

34:14.710 --> 34:20.290
♪♪

34:20.290 --> 34:21.920
[ Glass scrapes ]

34:21.920 --> 34:28.500
♪♪

34:28.500 --> 34:29.790
[ Piper groans ]

34:29.790 --> 34:31.620
Jo:
Oh, my God.

34:31.620 --> 34:34.380
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

34:34.380 --> 34:35.880
Okay.
I got you.

34:35.880 --> 34:37.580
[ Whimpers ]
You okay?

34:37.580 --> 34:39.880
Are you okay?
[ Inhales sharply ]

34:39.880 --> 34:41.920
Are you --
Are you hurt?

34:41.920 --> 34:43.960
Are you hurt?

34:43.960 --> 34:46.380
[ Panting ]

34:46.380 --> 34:49.330
♪♪

34:49.330 --> 34:52.000
H-- How?

34:52.000 --> 34:54.040
I-I don't know.

34:56.670 --> 34:59.500
It's okay.
It's okay.

34:59.500 --> 35:03.120
♪♪

35:07.000 --> 35:09.250
Chris: Freddie and Caitlyn
Martin's identities

35:09.250 --> 35:10.960
were fakes.

35:10.960 --> 35:13.580
And the prints
were not in the system.

35:13.580 --> 35:15.210
I could run their DNA
through the database,

35:15.210 --> 35:17.580
but I'm -- I'm pretty sure
that's a dead end, too.

35:18.920 --> 35:21.790
Uh, this was found
on the guy.

35:23.290 --> 35:25.710
What is it?

35:25.710 --> 35:28.080
Uh, nobody can
figure that out.

35:28.080 --> 35:30.500
Uh, no -- no circuitry,
no -- nothing magnetic.

35:32.790 --> 35:35.750
And, um,
NTSB reached out,

35:35.750 --> 35:38.170
said that plane
wasn't a plane at all.

35:38.170 --> 35:40.040
Uh,
unmanned drone.

35:41.290 --> 35:43.170
The National
Science Foundation

35:43.170 --> 35:46.080
mapping forest coverage.

35:46.080 --> 35:50.380
I mean,
I-I don't want to sound crazy,

35:50.380 --> 35:52.500
but, um...

35:52.500 --> 35:53.790
they're lying to us,
right?

35:59.000 --> 36:01.000
I mean,
you don't sound crazy.

36:03.580 --> 36:06.460
What is going on?

36:06.460 --> 36:08.290
I don't know.

36:10.580 --> 36:12.710
I think it has something to do
with Piper, though.

36:12.710 --> 36:14.750
Who -- Who's Piper?

36:14.750 --> 36:18.170
Oh, Piper is
the kid we found.

36:18.170 --> 36:21.420
Mia kind of...
gave her a name.

36:21.420 --> 36:22.750
Um...

36:25.080 --> 36:26.830
I'm, uh --
[ Sighs ]

36:28.880 --> 36:30.790
I'm not putting her
in the system.

36:34.170 --> 36:36.750
I'm keeping her
with me.

36:36.750 --> 36:39.960
Which is...

36:39.960 --> 36:42.000
very much not legal.

36:42.000 --> 36:45.830
♪♪

36:45.830 --> 36:50.960
And I'm gonna ask you
to do something equally illegal

36:50.960 --> 36:53.080
and keep it to yourself.

36:54.620 --> 36:57.670
Done. Easy.

36:57.670 --> 36:59.040
Don't -- Don't even
worry about it.

37:01.420 --> 37:02.790
Thanks, Chris.

37:05.960 --> 37:09.080
Jo: Hi, there.
[ Sighs ]

37:09.080 --> 37:11.040
Benny:
How'd you find me?

37:11.040 --> 37:13.000
Oh,
I have sources, too.

37:13.000 --> 37:16.080
Also, I've had a tail on you
since we first met.

37:16.080 --> 37:17.540
Thanks, Frankie.

37:17.540 --> 37:19.210
No problem,
Chief.

37:19.210 --> 37:20.790
Benny:
[ Chuckles ]

37:20.790 --> 37:22.210
Well played.
Oyster?

37:22.210 --> 37:24.500
Listen,
under normal circumstances,

37:24.500 --> 37:26.250
I would never
trust you.

37:26.250 --> 37:28.960
But right now,
I don't know who I can trust.

37:28.960 --> 37:29.790
That's an
excellent policy.

37:31.250 --> 37:33.880
♪ Doctor, my eyes ♪

37:33.880 --> 37:36.580
I did find out that
the phony government agents

37:36.580 --> 37:39.000
recovered and removed
the black box

37:39.000 --> 37:41.170
and human remains
from the crash site.

37:41.170 --> 37:42.540
♪ Just say
if it's too late for me ♪

37:42.540 --> 37:45.210
Does that change
your opinion of me at all?

37:48.120 --> 37:51.210
What are
you waiting for?

37:51.210 --> 37:52.880
You're a reporter.
Why don't you report this?

37:52.880 --> 37:54.500
Nah.

37:54.500 --> 37:57.210
You never write it until
you have the whole story.

38:04.380 --> 38:07.380
Maybe you can find out
what this is.

38:14.120 --> 38:15.290
I'll let you know.

38:22.460 --> 38:23.880
[ Keys clack ]

38:28.380 --> 38:32.120
Alright.
I see how it is.

38:32.120 --> 38:33.420
I go to work,

38:33.420 --> 38:36.920
and you steal my jacket
and my bed.

38:36.920 --> 38:39.580
Mia said
it was more comfortable.

38:39.580 --> 38:40.670
Oh, okay.

38:40.670 --> 38:43.580
[ Grunts ]

38:45.000 --> 38:48.460
♪♪

38:48.460 --> 38:50.120
You okay?

38:51.380 --> 38:53.210
Oh.

38:53.210 --> 38:57.460
Those people --
They're gone forever.

38:57.460 --> 38:59.000
Okay?

38:59.000 --> 39:02.540
And they can't ever
get to you again.

39:02.540 --> 39:04.580
I know.

39:04.580 --> 39:10.420
♪♪

39:10.420 --> 39:12.210
[ Sighs ]

39:12.210 --> 39:14.250
Do you think
I crashed that plane?

39:14.250 --> 39:16.210
No.

39:17.670 --> 39:19.210
I don't.

39:19.210 --> 39:20.460
I don't
think that at all.

39:20.460 --> 39:24.420
♪♪

39:24.420 --> 39:28.080
Well,
I am gonna go get changed.

39:28.080 --> 39:31.170
And as for you...

39:31.170 --> 39:34.290
I bought you
a toothbrush.

39:34.290 --> 39:35.790
Thank you.

39:35.790 --> 39:37.170
Mm-hmm.

39:37.170 --> 39:40.170
Go brush.

39:40.170 --> 39:43.250
♪♪

39:43.250 --> 39:46.080
[ Door closes ]

39:46.080 --> 39:48.000
[ Water running ]

39:48.000 --> 39:49.080
[ Spits ]

40:06.040 --> 40:08.670
[ Water trickling, echoing ]

40:10.460 --> 40:15.580
♪♪

40:15.580 --> 40:20.670
♪♪

40:20.670 --> 40:22.830
[ Water gurgling ]

40:25.670 --> 40:28.210
[ Water running ]

40:34.920 --> 40:37.500
[ Billie Eilish's "You Should
See Me in a Crown" plays ]

40:37.500 --> 40:41.080
♪ Bite my tongue, bide my time ♪

40:41.080 --> 40:44.000
♪ Wearing a warning sign ♪

40:44.000 --> 40:47.040
♪ Wait till the world is mine ♪

40:50.210 --> 40:53.380
♪ Count my cards,
watch them fall ♪

40:53.380 --> 40:56.580
♪ Blood on a marble wall ♪

40:56.580 --> 41:01.920
♪ I like the way
they a-a-a-all ♪

41:01.920 --> 41:03.210
♪ Scream ♪

41:03.210 --> 41:06.380
♪ Tell me which one is worse ♪

41:06.380 --> 41:09.380
♪ Living or dying first ♪

41:09.380 --> 41:14.040
♪ Sleeping inside a hearse ♪

41:14.040 --> 41:16.170
♪ I don't dream ♪

41:16.170 --> 41:18.580
♪ I'm okay ♪

41:18.580 --> 41:21.830
♪ I'm not your baby ♪

41:21.830 --> 41:27.170
♪ If you think I'm pretty ♪

41:27.170 --> 41:30.380
♪ You should see me in a crown ♪

41:30.380 --> 41:33.620
♪ I'm gonna run
this nothing town ♪

41:33.620 --> 41:35.000
♪ Watch me make 'em bow ♪

41:35.000 --> 41:37.120
♪ One by, one by ♪

41:37.120 --> 41:38.120
♪ One ♪

41:38.120 --> 41:40.170
♪ One by, one by ♪

41:40.170 --> 41:43.380
♪ You should see me in a crown ♪

41:43.380 --> 41:46.380
♪ Your silence
is my favorite sound ♪

41:46.380 --> 41:48.080
♪ Watch me make 'em bow
one by one ♪
